`,s.jsxs(e.p,{children:[s.jsx(e.strong,{children:"Supervised vs. unsupervised:"}),' In supervised learning you optimise a loss between predictions and known labels. In unsupervised clustering there are no labels: the algorithm must define and optimise a notion of "good grouping" from the data alone. This makes evaluation harder — but it also means clustering can discover patterns humans never anticipated.']}),`
