`,s.jsx(e.p,{children:"The range of domains where clustering delivers genuine value is broad:"}),`
`,s.jsx(e.h4,{children:"Customer segmentation"}),`
`,s.jsx(e.p,{children:'A retailer has 50,000 customers. Without knowing which "type" each customer is, K-means automatically finds groups — high-value loyalists, bargain hunters, seasonal shoppers — enabling targeted marketing campaigns.'}),`
`,s.jsx(e.h4,{children:"Image compression"}),`
`,s.jsx(e.p,{children:"Each pixel is a point in RGB space. Replacing 16 million possible colours with K = 256 cluster centroids reduces file size dramatically. JPEG and PNG both exploit variants of this idea."}),`
`,s.jsx(e.h4,{children:"Document grouping"}),`
`,s.jsx(e.p,{children:"News articles and research papers can be clustered by topic — politics, sport, science — without any pre-labeled categories. Search engines use this to surface related content."}),`
`,s.jsx(e.h4,{children:"Anomaly detection"}),`
`,s.jsx(e.p,{children:"Normal behaviour clusters tightly around a centroid. Anomalies — network intrusions, manufacturing defects, sensor faults — sit far from every cluster centre and are flagged automatically."}),`
`,s.jsx(e.h4,{children:"Gene expression analysis"}),`
`,s.jsx(e.p,{children:"Biologists cluster genes by expression patterns across experimental conditions to identify co-regulated pathways. This has revealed entire signalling cascades that no single experiment targeted."}),`
`,s.jsx(e.h4,{children:"City planning"}),`
`,s.jsx(e.p,{children:"Grouping neighbourhoods by demographic features — income, age distribution, commute patterns — helps governments allocate schools, clinics, and public transport where they are actually needed."}),`
